ly causes it? In an illuminating and elegantly written account of the widespread reduction of the world's wildlife, renowned paleontologist Niles Eldredge poses these questions and examines humankind's role in the larger life cycles of the earth, composing a provocative general theory of extinction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aBiodiversity. 0aEcology. 0aExtinction (Biology). 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Ecology.2bisacsh  aAdansonia.  aAesthetics.  aAlgae.  aAmerican Museum of Natural History.  aAmerican School of Classical Studies at Athens.  aAmherst College.  aArthropod.  aAwareness.  aBacteria.  aBasset Hound.  aBiodiversity.  aBiologist.  aBroad-billed roller.  aBrown University.  aCarnivore.  aCenozoic.  aComoro Islands.  aCretaceous.  aDarwinism.  aEast Africa.  aEcological crisis.  aEcology.  aEcosystem.  aEndemism.  aEocene.  aEvolution.  aExtinction event.  aExtinction.  aFlora.  aForest floor.  aFossil collecting.  aFuture Evolution.  aGenetic diversity.  aGeologist.  aGeology.  aGiant coua.  aGlobal temperature.  aGuineafowl.  aHerbivore.  aHolocene extinction.  aHominidae.  aHomo sapiens.  aHuman evolution.  aHuman eye.  aIan Tattersall.  aImagery.  aIn Specie.  aJellyfish.  aJurassic.  aLemur.  aLiving systems.  aLongevity.  aMammal.  aMesite.  aMesozoic.  aMiocene.  aMulticellular organism.  aNorthern Hemisphere.  aOligocene.  aOrdovician.  aOrganism.  aOutcrop.  aOverexploitation.  aPaleocene.  aPaleontology.  aPaleozoic.  aPermian.  aPheasant.  aPlant.  aPleistocene.  aQuaternary extinction event.  aQuinine.  aRainforest.  aReason.  aResult.  aRiver mouth.  aRock (geology).  aRocky shore.  aSediment.  aSedimentary rock.  aSerengeti.  